Nigerian pastor accused of abusing children who fled Boko Haram             AFP  29th Oct 2019 09:38:30 GMT +0300 AFP  29th Oct 2019 09:38:30 GMT +0300 AFP   Displaced: A 12-year-old girl who fled the Boko Haram insurgency in northeast Nigeria to join Pastor Solomon Folorunsho's camp. She left the camp earlier this year and lives with her family at an informal site for displaced people. [AFP]  Displaced: A 12-year-old girl who fled the Boko Haram insurgency in northeast Nigeria to join Pastor Solomon Folorunsho's camp. She left the camp earlier this year and lives with her family at an informal site for displaced people. [AFP] Displaced: A 12-year-old girl who fled the Boko Haram insurgency in northeast Nigeria to join Pastor Solomon Folorunsho's camp. She left the camp earlier this year and lives with her family at an informal site for displaced people. [AFP] Displaced: A 12-year-old girl who fled the Boko Haram insurgency in northeast Nigeria to join Pastor Solomon Folorunsho's camp. She left the camp earlier this year and lives with her family at an informal site for displaced people.         For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.                                                           Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. HERE. Related Topics Boko Haram Solomon Folorunsho Pastor Solomon International Christian Centre for Missions (ICCM) Nigeria